        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## Ranking of First-Row Divalent Transition Metals by log β₁ with Ammonia\n\nAll values below are from **NIST SRD-46**, for the equilibrium **M²⁺ + NH₃ ⇌ [M(NH₃)]²⁺** (β₁ = [ML]/[M][L]) in water at **25 °C, I = 0 M** (infinite dilution reference state).\n\n| Metal | log β₁ | vlm_id |\n|-------|--------|--------|\n| Mn²⁺ | **1.00** | vlm_173099 |\n| Co²⁺ | **2.11** | vlm_173133 |\n| Zn²⁺ | **2.37** | vlm_173205 |\n| Ni²⁺ | **2.80** | vlm_173181 |\n| Cu²⁺ | **4.31** | vlm_173157 |\n\n> **Fe²⁺** — No log β₁ entry was found at I ≤ 0.5 M in the database. This is unsurprising: Fe²⁺–NH₃ complexes in aqueous solution are very weak and the Fe²⁺/Fe³⁺ redox couple makes oxidation a persistent experimental problem, so reliable measurements are scarce.",
